data.description:
Welcome to the historic charm of the Vine Neighborhood in the heart of Kalamazoo! This captivating 5-bedroom, 2-full bath home, built in 1895, exudes character and potential. Currently configured as a main floor and upper floor duplex, this residence presents a unique opportunity for both investment and personal residence.

The main floor, currently owner-occupied, boasts timeless features including beautiful wood trim, baseboards, and hardwood floors throughout. The kitchen, equipped with LVT flooring and corner shelves, leads to a formal dining room with a convenient pantry. With 2 bedrooms and 1 bath, the upper floor unit, certified by the city, is rented until the end of April 2024 and has undergone several recent updates. At 2,212 square feet, this home offers ample space for comfortable living. Whether you choose to maintain the duplex configuration for rental income or convert it into a single-family residence, the possibilities are endless.

Enjoy the convenience of two parking spots behind the home, as well as included kitchen appliances and washer/dryer for both units. A full basement provides additional storage space and potential for further expansion or customization.

Located in the vibrant Vine Neighborhood, residents benefit from close proximity to downtown Kalamazoo's dining, shopping, and entertainment options, as well as nearby parks and recreational facilities.

Don't miss your chance to own a piece of history in this sought-after neighborhood. Whether you're an investor or looking to make this your forever home, this property offers the perfect blend of historic charm and modern convenience. Kalamazoo Schools. Schedule your showing today and imagine the possibilities!
